Cameron H. STEWART, Appellant v. UNION RAILROAD COMPANY, a corporation. No. 14693. United States Court oí Appeals Third Circuit. Argued May 19, 1964. Decided May 29, 1964. Paul F. Laughlin, Pittsburgh, Pa., (McArdle, Harrington, Feeney & McLaughlin, Pittsburgh, Pa., on the brief), for appellant. James R. Orr, Pittsburgh, Pa. (Reed; Smith, Shaw & McClay, Pittsburgh, Pa., on the brief), for appellee.

Before KALODNER, CANEY and SMITH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On review of the record we find no error. The judgment of the District. Court of October 30, 1963, will be affirmed.
